config BR2_PACKAGE_FORKED_DAAPD
	bool "forked-daapd"
	help
	  forked-daapd is a DAAP and RSP media server, whith support
	  for Linux and FreeBSD. It is a complete rewrite of mt-daapd
	  (Firefly Media Server).

	  DAAP stands for Digital Audio Access Protocol, and is the
	  protocol used by iTunes and friends to share/stream media
	  libraries over network.

	  RSP is Roku's own media sharing protocol. Roku are the marks
	  of the SoundBridge devices. See <http://www.roku.com>.
